description: This speceis group includes Kelp, Gopher, BlackandYellow, and Copper Rockfish young of the year. Individual rockfish that could be confidently identified to Copper/Gopher (Sebastes carnatus & S. caurinus) or Kelp (S. atrovirens) were recorded as such.  Individuals that could not be confidently to species, were count in the ‘KGBC’ complex that includes Kelp, Gopher, Black&Yellow, and Copper Rockfish. For example, no single individual was counted in both the Copper/Gopher and KGBC category.
